A1)Computer networks is a system that connects various computers together to share information.
Defination:Network Protocols are a set of rules governing exchange of information in an easy, reliable and secure way
Concept:When two people are speaking two different language we need a translator who can translate the language...similarly,when a data is shared between
two computer,there must exists a set of rules at both SENDER and RECIEVER end so that data can be recieved properly.

A2)Interpersonal communication is when both sender and reciever are a part of the same machine and the communciation between them are controlled by the Kernel.
Computer Networks deals with communication between sender and reciever which should be a part of different machines.
